  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Finding Solutions to the Coffee Rust Epidemic in Nicaragua</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective is to improve food security and resilience of 2,300 member families and partners, 38 primary cooperatives by restoring their main livelihood, coffee and food production, distributed in ten municipalities in the departments of Estel&#xED; , Madriz and Nueva Segovia . The overall plan includes rehabilitation of 2,387 acres, 4,435 Manzana renewal and maintenance of mean Manzana 3,700 per year. This plan also includes: food security and sovereignty , diversification and adaptation to climate change. Moreover, Heifer International in the Area of the Americas has the PROMISE COFFEE Program, which aims to strengthen food security and increase household incomes of small farmers in the region of Central America.</narrative>
  </description>
